# meddy — dev project on alien → https://meddy.<tailnet>.ts.net
#
# Standing route, on-demand backend. Unlike the other services there is NO app
# container here: this is a sidecar-only def (SVC_PROXY_HOST), so the tailnet
# device + cert stay live permanently while the actual backend is the meddy dev
# build you run from its git dir on alien. Requests to the URL return 502 until
# that build is listening on SVC_PORT — no per-run `tsvc up` needed.
#
# Bring the route up once (persists across reboots via restart: unless-stopped):
#   tsvc up meddy
#
# REQUIREMENT: the dev build must bind 0.0.0.0:SVC_PORT (not 127.0.0.1-only) so
# the userspace sidecar can reach it over host-gateway. Set SVC_PORT to whatever
# port the meddy dev server listens on.
SVC_PROXY_HOST=host.docker.internal
SVC_PORT=3000
EPHEMERAL=false
